tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
Dear Dr. Vinod Khanna

I am writing to express my deepest gratitude for the incredible care you have provided me in resolving my teeth problem that had plagued me for the past 20 years. Words cannot express how much your expertise and dedication have meant to me.

For two decades, I lived with several teeth issues. It caused me not only physical discomfort but also affected my confidence and self-esteem. I had consulted several dentists over the years, but none were able to provide a lasting solution.

Then I came to your practice, and everything changed. From the very first consultation, I felt a sense of hope and trust. You took the time to listen carefully to my concerns, thoroughly examine my teeth, and explain all the treatment options available in a clear and understandable way.

I was particularly impressed by the gentle touch, meticulous attention to detail, willingness to answer all my questions. You made me feel comfortable and confident throughout the entire treatment process.

And the results? They are nothing short of miraculous! Root Canal treatment my teeth are finally healthy, pain-free, and look absolutely amazing. I can smile with confidence again, and I can eat all the foods I used to avoid. It's truly a life-changing transformation.

Thank you, Dr. Vinod Khanna, for giving me back my smile and my confidence. You are a truly gifted dentist, and I am so grateful to have found you.

Sincerely,

[Hari Ram]
reply_text: Thanks for your detailed review.. Always good to hear how my treatment helps my patients.

tags: Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review: I didn't like the treatment plan. I already have crowns. I needed RCT in one of them as it wasn't done before. While other good dentists are able to do that without breaking the crown, they said they couldn't but that was ok. The thing that bothered me that they also charged for x-rays that they do to see the condition of tooth while I was carrying a full mouth x-ray with me. I visited 3 dentists and none of them charged for these x-rays as they do it with their own machines. Also, when I asked they even refused me mail me the copy even fter taking the amount. Highly unprofessional. Not recommended.
reply_text:
First of all the Xray u were carrying was an OPG which is not at all recommended for upper anterior teeth since it is hazy in that region adding to it u were giving a vague history of 3teeth RCT which was not at all evident in Xray. In order to be clear we took an Xray which we clearly mentioned that its chargeable if treatment is not carried out at our clinic because by your discussion we were able to make out that u already visited so many dentist as if it’s like a window shopping for u. N it’s very untrue that at we didn’t give u soft-copy of ur Xray. We told you that at if its ok we can mail you as soon as the doctor gets free with the patients but you demanded it within the very next minute so we clicked it and sent you through watsapp while you were sitting in the clinic.

So, it’s a humble request, kindly rectify your statements or its fine if you just visiting every dentist and finding faults and posting it here.
It’s our duty to give you the correct and ethical advice according to our expertise. If you don’t like our treatment options, you can straight aways discuss with us about other treatment options. But this is not the way.
